I've known Christiane for nearly 35 years. We were introduced through family when I was at ABC NEWS. She has since become my family. We've shared countless talks on every subject from Bosnia to boys and more. We've been through births, deaths, and divorces.  She is an incredible friend, confident, journalist and woman. 
•
She was diagnosed with Ovarian cancer this past Spring and, as is her way, faced it with intelligence and bravery. She is one of the lucky ones who caught it early and had successful surgery. But over 13,000 females die each year from this cancer which, if caught early,  is highly curable. 
•
Please listen to Christiane's message and talk to your girlfriends about it.  Women get all to accostomed to aches and pains every month since puberty and easily can dismiss it as more of the same. Be diligent. Make sure you get yearly checkups and don't let any doctor dismiss your discomfort and above all know your body and trust your instincts. #besties #girlfriends #ovariancancer #cancer #female ❤️

Something you didn’t know you needed today. ♥️

You don’t realize just how much you are craving live performances until you and 5 friends are invited to a very private, magnificent original interpretation of a holiday classic ballet, The Nutcracker. And this is why I love New York. The magic and talent is boundless. And yes, that’s a gorgeous Calder hanging in the background. #artonart 

This original work was created for, and filmed at Sotheby’s by brilliant NY City Ballet choreographer Peter Walker (@peteraltubewalker )

The interpretation was set to a modernized arrangement of the “Waltz of the Flowers” from The Nutcracker and performed by the gifted NYCB soloist Sebastien Villarini- Velez (@the_vinyl_seb ) and brilliant & divine Corps ballet member India Bradley (@indiabradleyy )

Click link to see  the full collaboration for Sotheby’s “Festival of Wonder”. https://www.sothebys.com/en/series/the-nutcracker-reimagined-a-collaboration-with-new-york-city-ballet?locale=enmy 

Thanks @sothebys @stellenevolandes @alejandracicognani
@david_monn

node.text:
Here’s the thing: Six years on a silly entertainment reality show will not negate the many accomplishments I had prior to #Rhony. Most of which the audience never saw, and all of which are part of an extraordinary life that I built for myself.  I wish the same for all the young women who also dream of leaving their small towns to move to the big city and make an interesting life for themselves. #female #solidarity #takeachanceonyou

It’s heartbreaking to listen to the news lately about what is happening in Afghanistan. In May of 2002, I flew with a small ABC crew from USAF base in Charleston to Khandahar. The ground war had recent ended but Khandahar was still considered a "hot zone." I  was embedded with the 101st Airborne Division, known as the "Rakkasans". We were on base with nearly 4,000 military personnel. We bonded in a way that you only get when you are given the task of covering a war. Needless to say the military personnel were wary of the press but I won them over by letting them have unlimited use of my satalite phone (thanks ABC💁🏼‍♀️). I still laugh at how much that bill was. It was a time before cell phones and What's App. 🤣💃

I've never written about my time in the war so perhaps that is my next book.  It's a painful time, mixed up with the grieving process of my husband and cousins who died just two years earlier. Maybe now is the right time now. 💙

The military people I encountered were the most incredible men and women I'd ever had the honor to know. I loved their bravery, their spirit and their awesome freestyle rap competitions every Friday night.  I filmed most of it, they were amazing!! Sadly the film was destroyed. I remember them all now and hope they have gone on to have great lives. I pray for the military and Afghans who are there as they try to build their country once again. 🙏💔
#afghanistan
